and (3) a log10 violin plot of the\n    `Distance.to.TSS` distribution per sample.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/homer_annot.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: homer_annot.pdf, homer_annot_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n", "name": "read_text_file", "tool_call_id": "call_nDHeubHNFueCU286UAdscdPf"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_7teEkpf3AOCfoBXKDQirnB9c", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the three input files: `sampleA_anno.txt`, `sampleB_anno.txt`, `sampleC_anno.txt`.\\n2. Extract the `Annotation` column and count occurrences of each first-token feature.\\n3. Create a summary table `homer_annot_summary.tsv` with counts per sample.\\n4. Generate a PDF `homer_annot.pdf` with three plots:\\n   - Stacked feature-proportion barplot.\\n   - Stacked distance-bin barplot (<2kb/<5kb/<10kb/>10kb).\\n   - Log10 violin plot of `Distance.to.TSS` distribution.\\n5. Validate the outputs and ensure they are saved in the `output/` directory.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (542 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_7teEkpf3AOCfoBXKDQirnB9c"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_QjyLC6Y5VO4FdGxWZ1KyxEmG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(ggplot2); library(dplyr); library(tidyr); library(readr); library(ggpubr); library(gridExtra)\\n\\n# Read input files\\nsampleA <- read_tsv('input/sampleA_anno.txt')\\nsampleB <- read_tsv('input/sampleB_anno.txt')\\nsampleC <- read_tsv('input/sampleC_anno.txt')\\n\\n# Function to extract first token from Annotation\\nextract_feature <- function(annotation) {\\n  sapply(strsplit(annotation, ' '), function(x) x[1])\\n}\\n\\n# Extract features\\nsampleA$Feature <- extract_feature(sampleA$Annotation)\\nsampleB$Feature <- extract_feature(sampleB$Annotation)\\nsampleC$Feature <- extract_feature(sampleC$Annotation)\\n\\n# Count features\\ncount_features <- function(data) {\\n  data %>% count(Feature)\\n}\\n\\ncountA <- count_features(sampleA)\\ncountB <- count_features(sampleB)\\ncountC <- count_features(sampleC)\\n\\n# Create summary table\\nsummary_table <- full_join(countA, countB, by = 'Feature', suffix = c('_A', '_B')) %>%\\n  full_join(countC, by = 'Feature') %>%\\n  rename(Count_C = n) %>%\\n  replace_na(list(n_A = 0, n_B = 0, Count_C = 0))\\n\\nwrite_tsv(summary_table, 'output/homer_annot_summary.tsv')\\n\\n# Plotting\\n# Feature proportion barplot\\nfeature_data <- summary_table %>% gather(Sample, Count, -Feature)\\nfeature_plot <- ggplot(feature_data, aes(x = Feature, y = Count, fill = Sample)) +\\n  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', position = 'fill') +\\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +\\n  labs(title = 'Feature Proportion')\\n\\n# Distance bin barplot\\nbin_data <- bind_rows(\\n  sampleA %>% mutate(Sample = 'A'),\\n  sampleB %>% mutate(Sample = 'B'),\\n  sampleC %>% mutate(Sample = 'C')\\n) %>%\\n  mutate(DistanceBin = cut(abs(Distance.to.TSS), breaks = c(-Inf, 2000, 5000, 10000, Inf),\\n                           labels = c('<2kb', '<5kb', '<10kb', '>10kb')))\\n\\nbin_plot <- ggplot(bin_data, aes(x = DistanceBin, fill = Sample)) +\\n  geom_bar(position = 'fill') +\\n  labs(title = 'Distance Bin Proportion')\\n\\n# Violin plot\\nviolin_plot <- ggplot(bin_data, aes(x = Sample, y = log10(abs(Distance.to.TSS)))) +\\n  geom_violin() +\\n  labs(title = 'Log10 Distance to TSS')\\n\\n# Save plots to PDF\\npdf('output/homer_annot.pdf')\\ngrid.arrange(feature_plot, bin_plot, violin_plot, ncol = 1)\\ndev.off()\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (542 chars) to .plan.md", "name": 